            <h1>Junichavand Village (Maliya Hatina)</h1>
            <p>An administrative unit in Junagadh, Gujarat</p>
        </header>
        
        <p>
            **Junichavand** is a village located within the **Maliya Hatina Taluka** of the **Junagadh District** in the state of Gujarat, India. Its primary role is local administration and agriculture.
        </p>

        <h2>Administrative Facts</h2>
        <div class="fact-box">
            <p><strong>District:</strong> Junagadh</p>
            <p><strong>Taluka (Tehsil):</strong> Maliya Hatina</p>
            <p><strong>State:</strong> Gujarat, India</p>
            <p><strong>Local Governance:</strong> Gram Panchayat</p>
        </div>

        <h2>Geographical Context</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>**Region:** Saurashtra Peninsula.</li>
            <li>**Proximity:** Located near the Arabian Sea coast, influencing its climate and agriculture.</li>
            <li>**Economic Base:** Primarily dependent on local agriculture (Groundnut, Cotton, etc.).</li>
        </ul>
